Spicy and Creamy Paneer Frankie The most delicious, flavoursome and filling meal 😍 Recipe: Ingredients: 1 TBSP Oil 1 Onion 1 Capsicum 1 TSP Garlic 1 to 2 Green Chillies 1 TBSP Red Chilli Powder 1 TSP Jeera Powder 1/2 TSP Coriander Powder A Pinch Of Turmeric Salt and Pepper To Taste 2 To 3 TBSP Curd or Fresh Cream 100 GMs Paneer 1 TBSP Fresh Coriander Method: -Heat Oil in a pan, add onion, capsicum, garlic and green chilli. Saute for 2 to 3 minutes. Do not overcook the veggies. -Add all the spices and curd/cream and cook on medium flame until well combined -Add the Paneer cubes and gently mix together -Top with fresh coriander Assembling the Frankie: Place the paneer filling on the roti or paratha Drizzle Green Chutney/Mint Mayo Top with Raw Onion rings. Serve immediately #paneer #frankie #roll #spicy #creamy #chutney #onion #recipe #recipes #easyrecipe #picklesandwine

🌿 Kosmal Waterfall Highlights: Location: Near Kosmal village, waghai area, Dang district. Type: Seasonal waterfall, best visited during or just after monsoon (July–October). Scenic Beauty: Surrounded by dense forests, small streams, and tribal settlements. Water Flow: Moderate; not a very tall or massive fall, but peaceful and ideal for nature lovers and trekkers. Local Vibe: A hidden gem not yet commercialized—expect minimal crowds. 🗺️ How to Reach: Nearest town: Waghai (~15-20 km away) From Waghai you might need to trek or use local guidance to reach the exact spot. 4-wheeler or bike is preferred due to rough rural roads. ✅ Travel Tips: Go with locals or a guide if you're unfamiliar with the forest paths. Wear trekking shoes and carry water/snacks. Network coverage is poor, so inform someone before you go. . . . Pack your bags, Dang is calling! Trisha sent an attachment.
Episode 1 of #SweetSummerTreats ☀, a series where I bring to you easiest dessert recipes to make your summer unforgettable😎 Summer means lots and lots of mango dessert, and this Mango Magnum is my latest obsession🥹🫶🏻 Made with only 4 ingredients, this recipe is a summer dream come true and a must try for all for mango lovers💛 Ingredients: 🥭1 mango 🥭¼ cup yogurt 🥭1 tbsp milk 🥭1 tbsp honey For the Chocolate Shell 🥭1 cup white chocolate 🥭1 tsp sunflower oil Instructions 1. Peel and cut a mango into pieces. Add it to a blender jar with the yogurt, milk and honey. Blend it all together to a smooth paste. 2. Add the mixture to popsicle moulds and insert an ice cream stick in the centre. Freeze the mango magnum for at least 8 hours or overnight. 3. For the chocolate shell, add the chopped white chocolate to a microwave safe bowl alongwith the sunflower oil and heat it in 30 second intervals, making sure to mix after each interval to prevent the chocolate from burning. 4. Demould the mango magnum and dip them in the melted chocolate to coat it well. Place it on a parchment paper and freeze it until the chocolate shell sets completely. bake with shivesh, shivesh bhatia, mango magnum, mango recipes, mango desserts, quick recipes, desserts, yummy, may, summer desserts, summer season, mango season
